73
00:12:21,405 --> 00:12:22,505
¡Hola, mi Yoshi!

74
00:12:27,725 --> 00:12:30,705
In the end, it was all because of a Yoshi!

75
00:12:30,985 --> 00:12:31,575
Yeah!

76
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:33,965
When we found that little boy, he...

77
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:36,245
Where did he go?

78
00:12:40,085 --> 00:12:41,805
He seemed nice, didn't you think?

79
00:12:48,145 --> 00:12:50,445
Hey, he does know it's my motorcycle, right?

80
00:13:31,887 --> 00:13:33,935
Where are you leading us?

81
00:13:34,435 --> 00:13:36,475
Try to enjoy it, princess.

82
00:13:36,735 --> 00:13:39,988
It's the last place you'll ever see alive!

83
00:14:36,494 --> 00:14:37,774
It's great, right?

84
00:14:38,355 --> 00:14:40,219
I know my dad will love it.

85
00:14:44,695 --> 00:14:46,274
Mommy, I'm scared!

86
00:14:46,675 --> 00:14:47,915
Everything is going to be alright.

87
00:15:02,415 --> 00:15:03,615
What in the Cave.

88
00:15:03,815 --> 00:15:06,095
Who brought a princess?

89
00:15:06,295 --> 00:15:07,295
Yeah!

90
00:15:07,915 --> 00:15:10,275
And I didn't bring just any princess.

91
00:15:10,475 --> 00:15:11,955
She is the guardian of the cosmos.

92
00:15:12,415 --> 00:15:14,175
The mother of stars!

93
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:17,635
With their powers, we're going to destroy the universe!

94
00:15:18,335 --> 00:15:21,382
She will give her life for our glory!

95
00:15:21,835 --> 00:15:22,445
Yeah!

96
00:15:22,495 --> 00:15:24,495
It was a good speech, wasn't it?

97
00:15:24,935 --> 00:15:26,935
It was direct and descriptive.

98
00:15:32,895 --> 00:15:36,615
Nobody touches my children!

99
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:42,355
¡Corre!

100
00:16:03,073 --> 00:16:06,035
The greatest battle of my life is approaching!

101
00:16:06,635 --> 00:16:09,455
The time has come to free my father!

102
00:16:16,074 --> 00:16:17,474
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, PRINCESS PEACH

103
00:16:34,053 --> 00:16:35,053
Do you think he'll like it?

104
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:38,915
Mario, do you feel something special for the princess?

105
00:16:39,155 --> 00:16:40,155
That?

106
00:16:40,975 --> 00:16:43,255
How can they think one can't give it to...

107
00:16:43,455 --> 00:16:44,735
The perfect gift for your friend...

108
00:16:45,235 --> 00:16:47,175
...so that he can see how much he cares?

109
00:16:47,975 --> 00:16:54,035
If the moon that's like a pizza appeals to you...

110
00:16:54,571 --> 00:16:56,254
a Peach.

111
00:16:56,535 --> 00:16:58,375
Didn't I fall in love with Peach?

112
00:17:00,975 --> 00:17:02,415
Let's go.

113
00:17:09,515 --> 00:17:10,515
Yeah!

114
00:17:13,295 --> 00:17:14,295
Say, Mushroom!

115
00:17:25,202 --> 00:17:26,115
Hello hello!

116
00:17:26,315 --> 00:17:27,555
Hello, Toad!

117
00:17:27,815 --> 00:17:28,895
You look amazing.

118
00:17:31,405 --> 00:17:32,515
And who is this?

119
00:17:33,395 --> 00:17:34,655
¿Yoshi?

120
00:17:35,295 --> 00:17:37,875
Nobody can resist this cute face.

121
00:17:40,255 --> 00:17:41,255
Come on!

122
00:17:42,235 --> 00:17:45,557
The dinosaur suddenly appears and is now part of the group.

123
00:17:53,215 --> 00:17:55,175
Hey, have you seen the princess?

124
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:32,185
Peach, you're missing your own party.

125
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:35,085
I hate birthdays.

126
00:18:36,125 --> 00:18:39,865
Yes. Luigi spent his tenth birthday crying.

127
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:42,375
He said his childhood was over.

128
00:18:44,237 --> 00:18:48,251
The funny thing about all this is that today isn't really my birthday.

129
00:18:48,765 --> 00:18:51,145
Today the Toads found me as a child.

130
00:18:51,845 --> 00:18:53,745
None of them have any idea where I come from.

131
00:18:54,965 --> 00:18:57,225
All my life I've wanted to know where he is...

132
00:18:57,425 --> 00:18:58,725
my whole family.

133
00:18:59,825 --> 00:19:01,005
It must be hard for you.

134
00:19:01,755 --> 00:19:04,905
Sometimes I feel so lost.

135
00:19:08,545 --> 00:19:12,763
Since it's not your birthday, I assume you don't want any presents.

136
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:14,115
¡Mario!

137
00:19:14,165 --> 00:19:16,325
Okay, it hurt.

138
00:19:26,436 --> 00:19:27,436
I love it!

139
00:19:53,412 --> 00:19:54,412
Look!

140
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:10,920
¡Mira!

141
00:21:26,545 --> 00:21:30,245
Princess Peach, I finally found you.

142
00:21:39,925 --> 00:21:41,105
Are you feeling better now?

143
00:21:44,005 --> 00:21:46,285
I can't believe that's you.

144
00:21:46,845 --> 00:21:50,385
Mom read us many bedtime stories about you.

145
00:21:51,025 --> 00:21:52,025
About me?

146
00:21:52,285 --> 00:21:53,285
Are you sure?

147
00:21:53,605 --> 00:21:55,905
He said that if anything ever happened to him,

148
00:21:56,105 --> 00:21:57,665
We would look for you and you would help us.

149
00:21:59,485 --> 00:22:00,065
Princess!

150
00:22:00,265 --> 00:22:01,925
My mom was kidnapped!

151
00:22:02,205 --> 00:22:03,085
But what happened?

152
00:22:03,285 --> 00:22:05,793
A robot takes her to an ugly planet.

153
00:22:06,005 --> 00:22:08,465
Beyond the Galaxy, Celestial Gate.

154
00:22:08,705 --> 00:22:09,705
Will you help us?

155
00:22:14,785 --> 00:22:15,785
Peach, sorry.

156
00:22:16,305 --> 00:22:16,835
I tried to...

157
00:22:16,885 --> 00:22:18,745
Yes, yes, we were spying, so what?

158
00:22:18,945 --> 00:22:20,406
Don't even think about leaving!

159
00:22:20,606 --> 00:22:22,985
Hey, can you give the princess a minute?

160
00:22:23,245 --> 00:22:24,725
She has everything under control.

161
00:22:24,965 --> 00:22:26,465
I disagree, Mario.

162
00:22:27,145 --> 00:22:28,925
Even though my pajamas say I'm your fan.

163
00:22:29,265 --> 00:22:32,645
There's nothing to know because she's not leaving.

164
00:22:33,593 --> 00:22:35,124
Okay, everyone outside.

165
00:22:35,324 --> 00:22:36,823
We'll discuss it in the morning.

166
00:22:39,328 --> 00:22:40,542
Rest, princess.

167
00:22:51,035 --> 00:22:52,905
Toad, pack our things.

168
00:23:40,875 --> 00:23:41,875
What do you mean he left?

169
00:23:42,295 --> 00:23:43,895
Yes, Mario left you this.

170
00:23:47,055 --> 00:23:50,375
Dear Mustache, I went to the Celestial Gate galaxy...

171
00:23:50,575 --> 00:23:51,976
to find the mother of this little girl.

172
00:23:52,176 --> 00:23:54,448
I leave the kingdom in your hands.

173
00:23:54,836 --> 00:23:57,041
Honestly, Peach.

174
00:23:59,261 --> 00:24:00,730
Sincerely?

175
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:02,495
Oh la la, that's a good sign!

176
00:24:02,695 --> 00:24:04,495
Has Princess Peach left?

177
00:24:04,855 --> 00:24:05,855
Oh, no!

178
00:24:10,415 --> 00:24:12,255
Please calm down!

179
00:24:13,855 --> 00:24:17,229
The Super Mario Brothers will be in charge of the kingdom temporarily.

180
00:26:00,365 --> 00:26:02,265
Ah, now what?

181
00:26:37,735 --> 00:26:38,735
Hey buddy!

182
00:26:40,335 --> 00:26:41,835
You scared me!

183
00:26:42,195 --> 00:26:43,335
What, did you want to see us?

184
00:26:43,815 --> 00:26:45,415
Stay there, I'll be right up.

185
00:26:48,515 --> 00:26:49,715
Time to absorb!

186
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:51,755
Clean the paint!

187
00:26:55,375 --> 00:26:58,055
And trim this bonsai!

188
00:26:58,255 --> 00:26:59,255
Here I go!

189
00:27:05,095 --> 00:27:06,355
Hello, Luigi!

190
00:27:08,055 --> 00:27:09,375
Hello, Mario.

191
00:27:11,395 --> 00:27:12,395
Admire!

192
00:27:12,575 --> 00:27:15,331
I've created a masterpiece for Princess Peach!

193
00:27:16,355 --> 00:27:17,355
How's it going, huh?

194
00:27:17,864 --> 00:27:19,012
Be completely honest.

195
00:27:20,645 --> 00:27:22,505
Wow, those are beautiful colors.

196
00:27:23,425 --> 00:27:26,585
Since you want my opinion, it's garbage.

197
00:27:27,405 --> 00:27:30,065
How dare you look at my masterpiece and say that?

198
00:27:30,265 --> 00:27:31,665
Do you think painting is easy?

199
00:27:32,085 --> 00:27:34,505
I'm going to rip the skin off your bones!

200
00:27:37,385 --> 00:27:40,985
Excuse me, it's old Bowser talking.

201
00:27:41,585 --> 00:27:44,685
I'm still confronting my demons.

202
00:27:46,105 --> 00:27:48,205
Okay, I feel better now.

203
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:51,185
As I was saying, it's not just a gift,

204
00:27:51,665 --> 00:27:53,225
It is a peace offering.

205
00:27:53,445 --> 00:27:55,977
I will ask him to release me, not for good behavior...

206
00:27:56,177 --> 00:27:57,940
For amazing behavior!

207
00:27:58,140 --> 00:27:59,785
Free yourself, forget it.

208
00:28:00,145 --> 00:28:02,200
And let's not even talk about him making you big again.

209
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:04,285
Even though I'm fully rehabilitated?

210
00:28:04,785 --> 00:28:06,585
Mario, if he's a different person now.

211
00:28:06,865 --> 00:28:09,045
In addition, we have a book club every week.

212
00:28:09,285 --> 00:28:10,465
Yes, I'll bring the soup.

213
00:28:10,765 --> 00:28:12,165
I don't trust you, monster.

214
00:28:12,365 --> 00:28:13,365
And especially not the princess.

215
00:28:15,265 --> 00:28:19,104
Either you start trusting me, or I'm going to rip your eyes out...

216
00:28:22,245 --> 00:28:24,245
Sorry, I didn't mean that...

217
00:28:25,605 --> 00:28:27,265
Okay, I won't bother you anymore.

218
00:28:27,465 --> 00:28:28,585
I'm going to go and rest.

219
00:28:28,945 --> 00:28:32,573
I need my eight hours of sleep, or seriously, I'll turn into a monster.

220
00:28:44,485 --> 00:28:45,485
Have a good rest!

221
00:31:19,665 --> 00:31:24,332
In the name of the Koopas, I order you to release my father.

222
00:31:26,305 --> 00:31:28,723
Over my dead body.

223
00:31:29,185 --> 00:31:30,505
So be it.

224
00:31:44,461 --> 00:31:45,965
Why don't we start again?

225
00:31:46,345 --> 00:31:47,446
And we all introduced ourselves.

226
00:31:47,646 --> 00:31:50,205
Okay, hi, I'm Luigi.

227
00:31:51,114 --> 00:31:54,396
I am Bowser Jr. and I've come to take my father away.

228
00:31:54,905 --> 00:31:55,905
Now!

229
00:32:39,864 --> 00:32:40,864
No.

230
00:33:18,205 --> 00:33:21,905
He was doing very well, but I came to give him a hand.

231
00:34:01,642 --> 00:34:02,642
That?

232
00:34:10,772 --> 00:34:11,772
Dad!

233
00:35:17,561 --> 00:35:18,663
Is everyone okay?

234
00:35:22,005 --> 00:35:23,425
Where are we?

235
00:35:30,750 --> 00:35:32,328
Sweet freedom!

236
00:35:33,045 --> 00:35:34,445
Oh no, it's a joke!

237
00:35:34,845 --> 00:35:36,265
Goodbye, idiots!

238
00:35:36,465 --> 00:35:37,985
Don't even think about running!

239
00:35:38,325 --> 00:35:38,935
¡No!

240
00:35:38,985 --> 00:35:40,725
You can't catch the wind!

241
00:35:45,525 --> 00:35:47,145
That's exactly what I did.

242
00:35:47,365 --> 00:35:48,945
It was a metaphor!

243
00:35:58,385 --> 00:35:59,385
Let go!

244
00:36:05,625 --> 00:36:07,525
Spit it out, it's going to hurt you.

245
00:36:14,445 --> 00:36:15,485
That was intense!

246
00:36:16,450 --> 00:36:18,965
I know, I feel really sorry for you.

247
00:36:19,445 --> 00:36:21,625
I'm still a mini work in progress.

248
00:36:22,425 --> 00:36:23,425
Excuse me, okay?

249
00:36:23,725 --> 00:36:27,697
And you expect me to shake hands with the turtle whose son tried to kill me?

250
00:36:28,345 --> 00:36:29,705
My son?

251
00:36:32,585 --> 00:36:34,985
I haven't seen my son in years.

252
00:36:36,145 --> 00:36:38,845
Mario, I've been a terrible father.

253
00:36:39,705 --> 00:36:40,765
He must hate me.

254
00:36:41,545 --> 00:36:42,355
Hate you?

255
00:36:42,405 --> 00:36:45,238
Your son tried to cut off my head to free you!

256
00:36:45,925 --> 00:36:47,205
He wants to see you.

257
00:36:48,105 --> 00:36:50,513
Perhaps, I don't know, he needs someone to guide him.

258
00:36:51,235 --> 00:36:52,235
Really?

259
00:36:52,645 --> 00:36:55,530
Do you think I still have a chance to reconnect with my boy?

260
00:36:56,405 --> 00:36:57,405
See, Mario?

261
00:36:57,605 --> 00:36:59,485
It is connected to his feelings.

262
00:37:00,385 --> 00:37:01,585
I'm drowning in them, Mario!

263
00:37:01,785 --> 00:37:03,225
Okay, let's keep walking.

264
00:37:03,605 --> 00:37:06,369
We need to figure out how to get off the planet and find Peach.

265
00:37:24,805 --> 00:37:25,805
¡Toad!

266
00:37:25,885 --> 00:37:26,885
There it is!

267
00:37:54,165 --> 00:37:55,965
The Celestial Gateway Galaxy!

268
00:38:02,935 --> 00:38:05,215
Welcome to the Celestial Gate Galaxy.

269
00:38:05,535 --> 00:38:07,175
Your Celestial Gateway to the galaxies.

270
00:38:12,742 --> 00:38:13,315
Toad,

271
00:38:13,365 --> 00:38:14,365
Where are you going?

272
00:38:14,745 --> 00:38:16,125
She's the one we're looking for!

273
00:38:19,723 --> 00:38:21,449
MISSING PRINCESS ROSALINA

274
00:38:40,605 --> 00:38:41,705
Princess?

275
00:38:42,465 --> 00:38:43,465
Are you OK?

276
00:38:49,508 --> 00:38:51,085
Did a Kiki get lost?

277
00:38:51,965 --> 00:38:54,325
Have you seen Kiki's friends?

278
00:38:56,205 --> 00:38:58,565
Poor little lost monkey!

279
00:38:58,845 --> 00:38:59,169
¡Ya, ya!

280
00:38:59,369 --> 00:39:00,725
I'll take care of you!

281
00:39:03,525 --> 00:39:04,585
That monkey!

282
00:39:04,785 --> 00:39:06,445
He uses his cuteness to steal!

283
00:39:06,985 --> 00:39:07,985
Toad, wait!

284
00:39:08,185 --> 00:39:10,385
Bring our boosters and coins!

285
00:39:10,605 --> 00:39:12,485
And my unfinished novel!

286
00:39:14,405 --> 00:39:15,405
Permission!

287
00:39:15,805 --> 00:39:16,225
Sorry!

288
00:39:16,425 --> 00:39:17,425
Excuse me!

289
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:28,795
It's ours now!

290
00:39:35,607 --> 00:39:37,215
The monkey went through the wall!

291
00:40:06,465 --> 00:40:07,865
Don't go away.

292
00:40:30,085 --> 00:40:31,085
Hey, you!

293
00:40:32,955 --> 00:40:33,945
Monkey of...

294
00:40:34,145 --> 00:40:36,100
Give me back my backpack.

295
00:40:43,976 --> 00:40:45,711
SCANNING IN PROGRESS

296
00:40:47,791 --> 00:40:49,735
Dad, I know you're out there somewhere.

297
00:40:51,975 --> 00:40:54,375
Sir, it's a lost cause.

298
00:40:54,675 --> 00:40:57,737
What matters most in our time of pain and sorrow is...

299
00:40:58,055 --> 00:41:00,535
Let's give each other strength!

300
00:41:01,755 --> 00:41:03,735
Hey, calm down, old man!

301
00:41:03,955 --> 00:41:05,795
We have to keep looking for my dad!

302
00:41:12,535 --> 00:41:15,775
Mario, Bowser wants to talk to you for a moment.

303
00:41:18,335 --> 00:41:19,335
You know, Mario?

304
00:41:19,595 --> 00:41:22,473
Every child thinks that their father is the greatest thing in the world.

305
00:41:23,315 --> 00:41:26,082
I don't want to disappoint my son by seeing me so small.

306
00:41:26,555 --> 00:41:28,875
I'm not going to make you big.

307
00:41:29,555 --> 00:41:31,415
You have always lived a small life.

308
00:41:32,275 --> 00:41:34,135
But I was born to be great!

309
00:41:34,835 --> 00:41:36,875
Undo the power of the Blue Mushroom!

310
00:41:37,095 --> 00:41:39,992
And I swear to fight by your side for all eternity!

311
00:41:40,335 --> 00:41:41,535
It's a great deal!

312
00:41:41,775 --> 00:41:43,295
Eternity is a long time!

313
00:41:43,675 --> 00:41:45,235
That's how we'll be unstoppable!

314
00:41:46,915 --> 00:41:47,915
No.

315
00:41:47,975 --> 00:41:49,195
Go ahead, hit me, Mario!

316
00:41:49,395 --> 00:41:50,165
¡Pégame!

317
00:41:50,215 --> 00:41:50,885
Yes, Mario, hit him.

318
00:41:51,085 --> 00:41:52,195
We can trust him.

319
00:41:52,395 --> 00:41:53,145
¡Pégame!

320
00:41:53,195 --> 00:41:54,255
Come on, don't be afraid!

321
00:41:54,495 --> 00:41:55,385
¡Dale!

322
00:41:55,435 --> 00:41:56,435
Hit me now!

323
00:41:56,995 --> 00:41:59,655
Pathetic and failed attempt at a plumber!

324
00:42:23,075 --> 00:42:25,395
You won't regret it!

325
00:42:29,895 --> 00:42:31,735
What are we waiting for?

326
00:42:31,935 --> 00:42:33,135
There's a castle over there!

327
00:42:33,335 --> 00:42:34,105
Come on!

328
00:42:34,155 --> 00:42:35,155
Follow me!

329
00:43:27,435 --> 00:43:28,464
Princess, look!

330
00:43:44,905 --> 00:43:48,565
Kiki, you brought something very good.

331
00:43:52,485 --> 00:43:55,685
Princesses are quite valuable.

332
00:43:57,885 --> 00:44:00,085
Kiki says your novel sucks!

333
00:44:06,645 --> 00:44:11,982
Why is it that princesses always let themselves be captured?

334
00:44:12,625 --> 00:44:14,685
Tell us what you know about the lost princess!

335
00:44:17,375 --> 00:44:19,705
I don't know anything!

336
00:44:21,045 --> 00:44:23,625
Listen to me carefully, you wart-faced bastard!

337
00:44:24,145 --> 00:44:26,925
You're going to tell me where to find Rosalina!

338
00:44:27,465 --> 00:44:28,484
Or what?

339
00:45:01,385 --> 00:45:03,145
Oh, princess!

340
00:45:03,345 --> 00:45:05,545
That's going to cost you dearly!

341
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:23,760
And!

342
00:46:50,724 --> 00:46:52,283
Where is it?

343
00:46:52,805 --> 00:46:54,905
Did I look like a snitch to you?

344
00:46:58,185 --> 00:46:59,605
Oh yes, I have it!

345
00:46:59,845 --> 00:47:01,245
Last chance!

346
00:47:01,525 --> 00:47:02,045
¡Ok, ok!

347
00:47:02,245 --> 00:47:03,195
Listen to me!

348
00:47:03,245 --> 00:47:04,445
Bowser's son has it!

349
00:47:04,745 --> 00:47:05,515
Where?

350
00:47:05,565 --> 00:47:07,165
In the nebula galaxy!

351
00:47:13,105 --> 00:47:14,105
¡Toad!

352
00:47:14,245 --> 00:47:15,245
Give me that!

353
00:47:18,165 --> 00:47:20,985
Call Bowser Jr. Now!

354
00:47:24,725 --> 00:47:26,745
Move those little paws, puppy!

355
00:47:30,245 --> 00:47:31,245
Hello.

356
00:47:31,565 --> 00:47:33,399
We are looking for a way to leave their planet.

357
00:47:33,846 --> 00:47:37,996
They have to talk to the queen, but the lizard-faced one stays here.

358
00:47:38,845 --> 00:47:40,285
I'll fix this.

359
00:47:46,955 --> 00:47:48,435
Greetings, Your Highness!

360
00:47:49,075 --> 00:47:52,061
We are trying to reach the Celestial Gate galaxy...

361
00:47:52,261 --> 00:47:55,494
They're the aliens who destroyed my flower field!

362
00:47:56,290 --> 00:47:57,276
Learn them!

363
00:47:57,476 --> 00:47:59,375
Take them to the honey mines!

364
00:48:01,895 --> 00:48:03,215
No, not if I can help it!

365
00:48:07,015 --> 00:48:09,875
Well, someone has to pay for their crimes.

366
00:48:10,075 --> 00:48:11,075
Arrest me!

367
00:48:11,155 --> 00:48:13,426
I will serve his sentence in his place!

368
00:48:14,275 --> 00:48:18,134
I can do the work of a hundred men and eat the food of about ten thousand bees!

369
00:48:18,905 --> 00:48:22,494
Lock me up and let them go to Heaven's Gate!

370
00:48:29,795 --> 00:48:31,275
We have a deal!

371
00:48:31,615 --> 00:48:33,475
Take them to the gates of heaven!

372
00:48:36,595 --> 00:48:37,975
Are you sure, Bowser?

373
00:48:40,575 --> 00:48:42,695
You're not as horrible as I thought.

374
00:48:43,655 --> 00:48:44,655
Thank you.

375
00:48:46,295 --> 00:48:47,595
Give me a hug!

376
00:48:49,726 --> 00:48:51,075
Take good care of it, okay?

377
00:48:51,755 --> 00:48:53,335
I always do that!

378
00:48:53,695 --> 00:48:57,115
This miserable insect will help them get through!

379
00:49:04,195 --> 00:49:05,165
Bye bye!

380
00:49:05,215 --> 00:49:06,795
Make your enemy proud!

381
00:49:29,015 --> 00:49:33,759
When I'm free, my sweetheart and I will go out dancing until the sun comes up.

382
00:49:34,174 --> 00:49:35,435
Do you have a sweetheart at home?

383
00:49:37,139 --> 00:49:41,133
He abandoned me at the altar and that hardened my black heart.

384
00:49:41,675 --> 00:49:45,225
Today I try to heal, remembering who I was before his love.

385
00:49:46,815 --> 00:49:48,235
You are a sensitive soul.

386
00:49:50,475 --> 00:49:51,475
That?

387
00:49:54,295 --> 00:49:55,335
Be strong!

388
00:49:55,835 --> 00:49:57,475
The right one for you will come along!

389
00:50:04,585 --> 00:50:05,585
¡Oh!

390
00:50:06,425 --> 00:50:07,785
Hi, Dad.

391
00:50:08,345 --> 00:50:09,345
¿Junior?

392
00:50:10,645 --> 00:50:12,005
My little one!

393
00:50:13,625 --> 00:50:15,325
Look how much you've grown!

394
00:50:16,465 --> 00:50:18,465
And all this is yours?

395
00:50:19,945 --> 00:50:22,405
Hey, shouldn't you be at boarding school?

396
00:50:22,725 --> 00:50:23,505
The boarding school?

397
00:50:23,705 --> 00:50:26,125
More like boring, because I was expelled.

398
00:50:27,665 --> 00:50:30,080
You grew into a real man while I wasn't looking, son.

399
00:50:30,723 --> 00:50:31,655
Dad!

400
00:50:31,705 --> 00:50:35,549
We're both going to become the most powerful guys in the universe!

401
00:50:36,425 --> 00:50:38,345
Do you remember when I was a little turtle?

402
00:50:38,565 --> 00:50:41,085
You worked so hard to conquer the world!

403
00:50:41,565 --> 00:50:43,288
But every now and then you took a break...

404
00:50:43,488 --> 00:50:46,863
And you would tuck me in and tell me our favorite story.

405
00:50:47,525 --> 00:50:49,792
Those were the best nights of my entire life!

406
00:50:50,785 --> 00:50:52,105
Tell me the story!

407
00:50:52,425 --> 00:50:53,545
Again?

408
00:51:08,068 --> 00:51:13,298
Long ago, there was a powerful villain with shining hair.

409
00:51:14,030 --> 00:51:15,933
He conquered everything in his path.

410
00:51:19,294 --> 00:51:21,735
And that villain had a son.

411
00:51:23,275 --> 00:51:26,930
The two of them traveled the universe eager to find a home.

412
00:51:27,475 --> 00:51:29,716
But every place they went was super...

413
00:51:29,916 --> 00:51:31,075
bored.

414
00:51:31,275 --> 00:51:32,275
Bored!

415
00:51:32,795 --> 00:51:34,755
And they created their own planet!

416
00:51:35,555 --> 00:51:36,555
Admire!

417
00:51:36,655 --> 00:51:37,895
Bowser's Planet!

418
00:51:38,555 --> 00:51:42,276
The sinister sanctuary where they would live out the rest of their days.

419
00:51:42,695 --> 00:51:44,915
With a roller coaster of evil.

420
00:51:45,295 --> 00:51:46,815
A gorge with lava.

421
00:51:47,215 --> 00:51:50,093
And a mountain they carved in the shape of their heads.

422
00:51:51,055 --> 00:51:54,947
And at the top of the planet, they built the biggest canyon of all.

423
00:51:55,635 --> 00:51:57,375
He could destroy the entire universe!

424
00:51:58,935 --> 00:52:00,015
Did they call him?

425
00:52:00,215 --> 00:52:01,949
Apocalyptic canyon!

426
00:52:02,315 --> 00:52:04,435
To get it moving, they needed...

427
00:52:04,635 --> 00:52:07,035
The most powerful princess in the universe!

428
00:52:07,715 --> 00:52:10,415
And once they extracted all its power,

429
00:52:10,615 --> 00:52:12,155
And the weapon was ready...

430
00:52:12,355 --> 00:52:15,055
They traveled from planet to planet, destroying everything...

431
00:52:15,255 --> 00:52:17,255
the one who had disrespected them.

432
00:52:17,675 --> 00:52:19,035
¡Boom!

433
00:52:19,395 --> 00:52:20,395
¡Boom!

434
00:52:21,040 --> 00:52:25,872
Until they danced on the ashes of the universe, like supreme kings!

435
00:52:26,915 --> 00:52:27,915
The end.

436
00:52:28,775 --> 00:52:31,455
Will you tell me tomorrow night, Daddy?

437
00:52:31,655 --> 00:52:32,655
Of course.

438
00:52:33,175 --> 00:52:34,195
Rest, my little one.

439
00:52:41,035 --> 00:52:42,035
Well!

440
00:52:42,195 --> 00:52:43,875
I finally built the planet!

441
00:52:44,195 --> 00:52:45,195
Did you do it?

442
00:52:45,435 --> 00:52:46,775
We're traveling to it!

443
00:52:47,255 --> 00:52:48,225
Together, Dad!

444
00:52:48,275 --> 00:52:49,355
¡Dos Bowsers!

445
00:52:49,935 --> 00:52:50,935
Unlimited!

446
00:52:55,175 --> 00:53:00,115
My lords, we have a little problem.

447
00:53:16,815 --> 00:53:18,835
Welcome to the information center.

448
00:53:19,115 --> 00:53:20,211
My name is Rob.

449
00:53:20,411 --> 00:53:22,195
Do you need information?

450
00:53:22,755 --> 00:53:23,995
We need a pilot.

451
00:53:24,195 --> 00:53:25,085
It's urgent.

452
00:53:25,135 --> 00:53:25,925
With pleasure.

453
00:53:25,975 --> 00:53:28,075
The pilots are on the flight deck,

454
00:53:28,275 --> 00:53:29,285
which is located right...

455
00:53:38,015 --> 00:53:38,905
Oh, Rob!

456
00:53:38,955 --> 00:53:40,295
You're killing me!

457
00:53:40,755 --> 00:53:41,755
I'm sorry.

458
00:53:41,875 --> 00:53:43,295
I don't want to kill you.

459
00:53:44,275 --> 00:53:44,795
¡Toad!

460
00:53:44,995 --> 00:53:45,815
I'm Rob.

461
00:53:46,015 --> 00:53:46,805
I know!

462
00:53:46,855 --> 00:53:47,405
GOOD.

463
00:53:47,455 --> 00:53:49,015
Thank you for visiting this center.

464
00:53:49,215 --> 00:53:50,880
Where is the cover?

465
00:53:51,080 --> 00:53:52,148
This...

466
00:53:55,895 --> 00:53:57,955
-...here. - Thank you!

467
00:53:58,175 --> 00:53:59,175
You are welcome.

468
00:54:48,575 --> 00:54:50,195
I can't believe it!

469
00:54:51,634 --> 00:54:52,398
Hello!

470
00:54:52,598 --> 00:54:54,936
Would you take us to the Nebula Galaxy, sir?

471
00:54:55,515 --> 00:54:56,515
No.

472
00:54:58,275 --> 00:55:01,435
Excuse me, how much to take us to the Nebula Galaxy?

473
00:55:01,755 --> 00:55:03,455
Very dangerous for this cute pilot!

474
00:55:04,312 --> 00:55:05,775
Okay, explain it to me.

475
00:55:06,595 --> 00:55:10,422
Why would a princess try to go to the most dangerous place in the galaxy?

476
00:55:11,095 --> 00:55:12,415
Who are you?

477
00:55:12,675 --> 00:55:14,715
Don't ask me personal questions.

478
00:55:15,335 --> 00:55:16,475
Oh, forgive me, I didn't mean to...

479
00:55:16,675 --> 00:55:18,215
¡Soy Fox McCloud!

480
00:55:19,595 --> 00:55:23,555
Leader of the legendary team, Star Fox!

481
00:55:23,896 --> 00:55:25,415
Only three things matter to me.

482
00:55:25,615 --> 00:55:27,115
Keeping the Lylat system safe,

483
00:55:27,315 --> 00:55:30,788
fighting alongside my friends and doing extreme barrel rolls.

484
00:55:31,195 --> 00:55:33,615
I mean, barrel rolls, dudes!

485
00:55:34,355 --> 00:55:36,695
But one day, my Warp Drive exploded.

486
00:55:37,255 --> 00:55:39,136
It tore a giant hole in the tissue of the...

487
00:55:39,336 --> 00:55:42,096
time and space and it absorbed me into another universe.

488
00:55:42,395 --> 00:55:44,332
That's what I get for having a frog as an engineer.

489
00:55:44,775 --> 00:55:47,825
Now I travel the galaxy in search of a way home.

490
00:55:48,355 --> 00:55:50,815
Doing good, if they can afford me.

491
00:55:51,875 --> 00:55:53,855
Oh, and I also have some super cool boots.

492
00:55:56,755 --> 00:55:58,360
Now that's a good origin story...

493
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:00,295
Who is going to take us to the Nebula Galaxy?

494
00:56:01,235 --> 00:56:04,062
Did I look desperate, like I was starving?

495
00:56:07,505 --> 00:56:08,685
Okay, deal.

496
00:56:09,005 --> 00:56:11,339
I'll refuel the Air Wing and we'll be off in five, gentlemen.

497
00:56:16,065 --> 00:56:19,715
That's the coolest guy I've ever seen!

498
00:56:26,185 --> 00:56:28,645
Mario, I have a great idea.

499
00:56:29,065 --> 00:56:31,885
When you see Peach, go up to her and say, oh,

500
00:56:32,085 --> 00:56:33,035
blah, blah, blah.

501
00:56:33,085 --> 00:56:34,205
Oh, hi, how are you?

502
00:56:34,405 --> 00:56:38,396
And then, boom!, you ask her out on a date.

503
00:56:38,865 --> 00:56:39,865
I don't know, Lu.

504
00:56:40,125 --> 00:56:42,805
Would a princess go on a date with a plumber?

505
00:56:44,585 --> 00:56:48,965
Mario would be the luckiest princess in the world...

506
00:56:49,165 --> 00:56:50,205
if she were your girlfriend.

507
00:56:50,830 --> 00:56:52,625
I know she's going to say yes.

508
00:56:52,845 --> 00:56:56,448
And you're going to ask her if she has a friend for me.

509
00:56:57,605 --> 00:57:00,365
Now, we just have to find her.

510
00:57:01,045 --> 00:57:04,956
That's fair, because...

511
00:57:09,965 --> 00:57:11,439
¡Peach!

512
00:57:11,645 --> 00:57:12,645
¿Mario?

513
00:57:15,305 --> 00:57:17,625
Ah, train a Yoshi.

514
00:57:18,905 --> 00:57:19,905
¡Mario!

515
00:57:21,905 --> 00:57:22,905
So what?

516
00:57:23,825 --> 00:57:26,245
Shaking hands is cool, I mean...

517
00:57:26,445 --> 00:57:28,561
Shaking hands is cool, I thought you'd like it...

518
00:57:29,425 --> 00:57:30,375
Because it's cool.

519
00:57:30,425 --> 00:57:30,995
¡Mario!

520
00:57:31,045 --> 00:57:32,665
I discovered where Rosalina is.

521
00:57:33,045 --> 00:57:34,765
And he said he's going to take us.

522
00:57:42,025 --> 00:57:43,065
Beautiful ship!

523
00:57:43,505 --> 00:57:44,565
Nice mustache.

524
00:57:45,905 --> 00:57:46,905
Come one, come all!

525
00:58:07,365 --> 00:58:09,745
It's the life of a space rebel!

526
00:58:10,285 --> 00:58:14,072
I don't see him as that rebellious, he's like Mrs. Cacelato's dog.

527
00:58:14,345 --> 00:58:16,503
And does Mrs. Cacelato's dog do this?

528
00:58:23,405 --> 00:58:25,365
I like this handsome guy!

529
00:58:35,537 --> 00:58:37,432
AIM

530
00:58:40,755 --> 00:58:42,525
You'd better hold on to whatever you can!

531
00:58:47,214 --> 00:58:48,214
Olé!

532
00:59:02,765 --> 00:59:04,805
Grrr!

533
00:59:20,805 --> 00:59:21,365
Grrr!

534
00:59:21,565 --> 00:59:22,765
They're going to pay for that!

535
00:59:28,485 --> 00:59:28,985
Wait!

536
00:59:29,185 --> 00:59:29,465
¡Junior!

537
00:59:29,665 --> 00:59:30,925
I've already lived with them!

538
00:59:31,505 --> 00:59:35,145
They're pathetic, but it makes me sad to kill them!

539
00:59:35,925 --> 00:59:37,625
Are you saying it's better if we don't kill them?

540
00:59:39,365 --> 00:59:40,965
That's strange...

541
00:59:41,165 --> 00:59:41,715
¡Ok!

542
00:59:41,765 --> 00:59:43,085
I'm doing this for you, Dad!

543
00:59:43,525 --> 00:59:46,982
When I'm done with them, they'll be begging for their mommies!

544
00:59:48,305 --> 00:59:49,348
And what does that do, Junior?

545
00:59:57,465 --> 00:59:58,465
Bowser!

546
00:59:58,665 --> 00:59:59,805
He saw through our faces!

547
01:00:12,525 --> 01:00:12,985
Oh!

548
01:00:13,185 --> 01:00:14,325
He made them babies!

549
01:00:32,530 --> 01:00:33,725
Don't worry, Dad.

550
01:00:33,945 --> 01:00:38,577
By this time tomorrow, you'll have forgotten all about those slimy guys in overalls.

551
01:00:39,165 --> 01:00:41,185
The whole universe is going to be ours!

552
01:01:06,713 --> 01:01:07,713
Is it working now?

553
01:01:08,835 --> 01:01:09,915
No.

554
01:01:12,042 --> 01:01:13,063
Toad, the babies.

555
01:01:14,906 --> 01:01:15,487
That?

556
01:01:15,687 --> 01:01:16,687
I'm coming!

557
01:01:22,444 --> 01:01:23,444
Come here!

558
01:01:53,035 --> 01:01:54,035
¡Yoshi!

559
01:01:54,175 --> 01:01:55,175
Come back!

560
01:01:55,535 --> 01:01:56,595
¡Yoshi!

561
01:01:57,055 --> 01:01:58,055
¡Yoshi!

562
01:02:13,857 --> 01:02:15,031
¡Luigi!

563
01:02:17,603 --> 01:02:18,603
Kid, get down from there!

564
01:02:27,351 --> 01:02:28,351
¡Mario!

565
01:02:57,685 --> 01:02:59,350
¡Yoshi!

566
01:03:29,805 --> 01:03:31,453
No. Let it go, it's not a toy!

567
01:03:31,653 --> 01:03:32,799
Let it go, give it to me!

568
01:03:33,385 --> 01:03:34,605
Let her go, kid!

569
01:04:57,771 --> 01:05:00,025
Honestly, I did enjoy being a baby, the ideas...

570
01:05:00,225 --> 01:05:03,185
The terrifying things that haunted me disappeared, it was nice.

571
01:05:05,025 --> 01:05:07,125
We're going to make you feel like new, okay?

572
01:05:07,705 --> 01:05:09,445
You'll be fine, it's just a scratch.

573
01:05:09,905 --> 01:05:11,365
It's a scratch!

574
01:05:11,565 --> 01:05:12,565
¡Oh no!

575
01:05:22,845 --> 01:05:25,205
Don't worry, we'll find a way to get off the planet.

576
01:05:25,405 --> 01:05:28,325
Mario, we're galaxies away from Rosalina, the ship...

577
01:05:28,525 --> 01:05:32,094
There's no way around it, and the strangest thing is, we have another dinosaur!

578
01:05:33,885 --> 01:05:35,705
I know you're frustrated.

579
01:05:35,965 --> 01:05:37,205
Princesses don't get frustrated!

580
01:05:38,085 --> 01:05:41,365
Okay, so can I not be frustrated with you?

581
01:05:49,855 --> 01:05:52,835
Okay, testing, testing, here Green, Stop, Red,

582
01:05:53,035 --> 01:05:54,155
Chaparro and Sorron, dog.

583
01:05:54,535 --> 01:05:56,954
We request an immediate evacuation.

584
01:05:57,555 --> 01:05:59,755
We crashed in the middle of Dinoland.

585
01:06:00,135 --> 01:06:02,715
We're bringing a royal cargo...

586
01:06:03,135 --> 01:06:03,695
Leave him alone!

587
01:06:03,895 --> 01:06:05,055
Let's watch it!

588
01:06:15,915 --> 01:06:19,124
This is what happens when they don't go to sleep on time.

589
01:06:20,591 --> 01:06:24,482
Mayday Mayday, Luigi the Fabulous is signing off, over and out!

590
01:06:24,682 --> 01:06:26,486
¡LUIIIIGIIIIIIIII!

591
01:06:35,845 --> 01:06:40,197
Their mustaches were ridiculous, but they weren't bad people.

592
01:06:40,965 --> 01:06:42,605
They were your friends, weren't they?

593
01:06:43,165 --> 01:06:45,445
Nothing is more dangerous than a friend!

594
01:06:45,645 --> 01:06:49,457
When you let your guard down, you get stabbed in the back.

595
01:06:49,657 --> 01:06:51,385
Where did you hear that?

596
01:06:51,785 --> 01:06:54,889
That's what you told me when you took me to my first day of school.

597
01:06:55,358 --> 01:07:01,036
- Yes, I'm a good father. - Those friends of yours wanted to ruin you.

598
01:07:01,381 --> 01:07:03,139
Becoming something you are not.

599
01:07:03,974 --> 01:07:05,242
Do you know who won't hurt you?

600
01:07:06,004 --> 01:07:09,874
Your family. Family is forever.

601
01:07:10,925 --> 01:07:11,925
Close your eyes.

602
01:07:17,511 --> 01:07:18,783
Dad!

603
01:07:19,155 --> 01:07:20,402
Don't cheat.

604
01:07:21,847 --> 01:07:22,997
Now open them.

605
01:07:41,258 --> 01:07:42,258
Hey!

606
01:07:42,769 --> 01:07:45,483
An extremely rare object is coming this way.

607
01:08:04,195 --> 01:08:07,455
Here we go!

608
01:08:26,015 --> 01:08:29,645
We'll reach the nebula galaxy before the party!

609
01:09:12,395 --> 01:09:18,321
A long time ago there lived a brave and noble princess named Peach.

610
01:09:21,607 --> 01:09:24,832
Their story begins many years ago.

611
01:09:26,146 --> 01:09:30,698
When she lived on a small planet with her sister Rosalina.

612
01:09:31,569 --> 01:09:34,897
Both were made of stardust.

613
01:09:39,864 --> 01:09:44,253
Their love burned as brightly as the stars themselves.

614
01:09:46,147 --> 01:09:50,070
Together they could invoke the power of the cosmos.

615
01:10:03,161 --> 01:10:07,057
But the forces of evil wanted to obtain that power.

616
01:10:09,683 --> 01:10:13,126
Rosalina had to send Peach away,

617
01:10:13,641 --> 01:10:15,290
to a safe place.

618
01:10:32,070 --> 01:10:38,304
The Toads raised and protected her, until she was strong enough to protect them.

619
01:10:55,978 --> 01:10:56,978
Dad!

620
01:10:57,295 --> 01:11:00,168
Welcome to Bowser's planet!

621
01:11:19,741 --> 01:11:21,913
Did you build the planet all by yourself?

622
01:11:22,113 --> 01:11:23,235
But that's not all!

623
01:11:23,475 --> 01:11:27,295
We have our very own apocalyptic cannon!

624
01:11:30,811 --> 01:11:34,495
And the princess I kidnapped to enhance it!

625
01:11:38,591 --> 01:11:41,075
The universe will never forgive them!

626
01:11:41,555 --> 01:11:43,095
This is who you are!

627
01:11:43,615 --> 01:11:45,395
This is where you belong!

628
01:11:45,655 --> 01:11:48,335
Tonight we will destroy the Mushroom Kingdom!

629
01:11:48,715 --> 01:11:50,535
And tomorrow, the universe!

630
01:11:57,095 --> 01:12:01,093
Bowser!

631
01:12:01,293 --> 01:12:03,995
Yes, long live the king!

632
01:12:05,335 --> 01:12:06,635
They're waiting for your return!

633
01:12:09,284 --> 01:12:14,391
Sometimes you can lose your way on life's rainbow path.

634
01:12:14,591 --> 01:12:15,725
But hopefully!

635
01:12:16,425 --> 01:12:21,060
A mini version of yourself helps you remember your true nature.

636
01:12:21,684 --> 01:12:24,115
What's in the Cave?

637
01:12:24,815 --> 01:12:26,755
Your king has returned!

638
01:13:33,926 --> 01:13:35,460
We'll bring them down to the planet!

639
01:13:36,247 --> 01:13:39,648
Get ready, things are about to get crazy!

640
01:13:41,511 --> 01:13:44,233
Team Star Fox! Ready!

641
01:13:46,458 --> 01:13:47,735
And!

642
01:14:14,905 --> 01:14:15,905
¡Agarrense!

643
01:14:21,704 --> 01:14:23,121
Something's coming!

644
01:14:27,304 --> 01:14:28,751
Do your thing, McCloud.

645
01:14:31,982 --> 01:14:32,982
And!

646
01:14:45,365 --> 01:14:46,365
Good luck!

647
01:15:30,905 --> 01:15:33,362
I don't know what it means!

648
01:15:33,562 --> 01:15:36,127
Let them go that way and we'll stay this way!

649
01:15:36,445 --> 01:15:37,445
Ah, I understand now!

650
01:16:20,145 --> 01:16:21,145
¡Oh!

651
01:16:27,935 --> 01:16:29,415
Intruder alert!

652
01:16:29,615 --> 01:16:30,705
Intruder alert!

653
01:16:30,905 --> 01:16:32,145
Catch them!

654
01:16:36,585 --> 01:16:38,075
Just a little more and that's it, dude!

655
01:16:40,585 --> 01:16:41,585
My lords!

656
01:16:41,815 --> 01:16:43,995
The tormentors have returned!

657
01:16:45,515 --> 01:16:47,195
Let me handle it!

658
01:16:48,155 --> 01:16:51,149
Build a top-level security system.

659
01:16:54,775 --> 01:16:57,075
They're going to be torn to pieces!

660
01:16:58,735 --> 01:17:00,415
I love being your dad!

661
01:17:00,755 --> 01:17:04,314
Oh, and the days are long, but the years are short!

662
01:17:26,435 --> 01:17:27,455
Hello, Pichimario!

663
01:17:30,535 --> 01:17:33,035
Get ready to see your creator!

664
01:17:41,381 --> 01:17:42,558
Yes, yes, yes, yes!

665
01:17:42,758 --> 01:17:43,935
Yes, yes, yes!

666
01:18:44,825 --> 01:18:45,862
Now I have them!

667
01:19:23,196 --> 01:19:25,872
I'm not going to let them ruin your plan, son!

668
01:19:47,770 --> 01:19:48,770
Bowser!

669
01:19:51,305 --> 01:19:52,985
It didn't have to end like this!

670
01:19:53,405 --> 01:19:56,041
I know there's still a little goodness left in you!

671
01:20:02,983 --> 01:20:03,983
Let us through!

672
01:20:04,195 --> 01:20:05,005
Now!

673
01:20:05,055 --> 01:20:06,055
Or what?

674
01:20:06,235 --> 01:20:08,135
Are they going to humiliate me at my wedding?

675
01:20:08,530 --> 01:20:11,099
Shrink up like an insect and get into a jar?

676
01:20:11,602 --> 01:20:13,835
Should I join a book club, too?

677
01:20:14,222 --> 01:20:15,835
We had a great time, Mario!

678
01:20:16,315 --> 01:20:18,015
But Bowser is back!

679
01:20:18,335 --> 01:20:20,555
And they will feel my full fury!

680
01:20:47,555 --> 01:20:48,597
Dad!

681
01:21:31,274 --> 01:21:33,385
I am the lord of bones!

682
01:21:33,585 --> 01:21:36,085
I am the skeleton king!

683
01:21:36,285 --> 01:21:38,165
And I am his son!

684
01:21:53,785 --> 01:21:54,785
¡Mario!

685
01:21:56,765 --> 01:21:57,765
¡Corre!

686
01:21:58,405 --> 01:21:59,405
¡Scarf!

687
01:23:07,543 --> 01:23:08,543
Yes, yes, yes!

688
01:23:13,925 --> 01:23:14,995
¡Yoshi!

689
01:23:20,187 --> 01:23:21,575
How odd!

690
01:24:28,338 --> 01:24:29,684
Stop this, Lu!

691
01:24:36,122 --> 01:24:37,270
- Lu! - What?

692
01:24:37,470 --> 01:24:39,490
You already know I'm not good at drawing!

693
01:24:51,350 --> 01:24:52,350
And!

694
01:25:29,215 --> 01:25:31,475
In the name of the Koopas!

695
01:25:34,475 --> 01:25:35,755
Son!

696
01:25:36,455 --> 01:25:37,445
Dad!

697
01:25:37,645 --> 01:25:38,645
Help me!

698
01:25:43,255 --> 01:25:44,715
¡Junior!

699
01:26:18,553 --> 01:26:21,141
- Dad! - My boy!

700
01:26:52,771 --> 01:26:53,859
Rosalina!

701
01:27:01,303 --> 01:27:03,538
I need you to try!

702
01:27:56,239 --> 01:27:58,195
I knew you would come for me.

703
01:28:02,119 --> 01:28:02,867
¡Mira!

704
01:28:03,067 --> 01:28:04,565
I found your femur, Dad!

705
01:28:04,905 --> 01:28:05,985
You're okay, Junior.

706
01:28:06,285 --> 01:28:07,285
Let's find my foot.

707
01:28:08,785 --> 01:28:09,785
¡Mario!

708
01:28:10,105 --> 01:28:11,055
¡Mario!

709
01:28:11,105 --> 01:28:12,645
She's my sister, Rosalina!

710
01:28:13,625 --> 01:28:16,125
It's great that they finally found each other.

711
01:28:16,325 --> 01:28:18,405
Oh, I love it when families get together!

712
01:28:32,045 --> 01:28:33,045
Mother?

713
01:28:33,225 --> 01:28:34,225
Mother!

714
01:28:34,845 --> 01:28:35,945
Mother!

715
01:28:36,485 --> 01:28:36,535
Mother!

716
01:28:36,705 --> 01:28:37,965
My babies!

717
01:28:39,005 --> 01:28:40,725
We miss you so much!

718
01:28:41,085 --> 01:28:42,485
I missed them a lot too.

719
01:28:42,685 --> 01:28:46,025
Mommy, can we visit the Mushroom Kingdom?

720
01:28:46,225 --> 01:28:47,445
I want to see the castle!

721
01:28:48,125 --> 01:28:49,805
OK that's fine.

722
01:28:56,765 --> 01:28:58,365
Hey, what about the castle?

723
01:29:00,345 --> 01:29:03,149
Ah, well, the castle, that castle, ah...

724
01:29:03,349 --> 01:29:05,251
He died!

725
01:29:06,585 --> 01:29:08,705
And what does that mean?

726
01:29:09,449 --> 01:29:10,449
Let me tell you something?

727
01:29:10,585 --> 01:29:11,465
We are going to rebuild.

728
01:29:11,665 --> 01:29:13,445
The best castle of all!

729
01:29:13,645 --> 01:29:14,645
Who wants to help?

730
01:29:20,057 --> 01:29:21,417
Oh, yes!

731
01:32:19,936 --> 01:32:21,160
SUPER MARIO GALAXY THE MOVIE

732
01:32:25,155 --> 01:32:26,795
What's your next stop?

733
01:32:27,095 --> 01:32:29,675
That lovely space princess repaired my warp drive...

734
01:32:29,875 --> 01:32:30,755
And I'm going home.

735
01:32:32,895 --> 01:32:33,895
Good luck with them!

736
01:32:34,295 --> 01:32:36,295
They are a rather peculiar family.

737
01:32:45,575 --> 01:32:46,695
Patience, son.

738
01:32:47,355 --> 01:32:48,995
No prison will hold us.

739
01:32:49,375 --> 01:32:50,555
We'll be leaving soon.

740
01:32:59,515 --> 01:33:00,955
Hello, lizards.

741
01:33:01,275 --> 01:33:02,435
Are they trying to escape?

742
01:33:03,295 --> 01:33:05,855
Are they going to obey my rules?

743
01:33:06,255 --> 01:33:07,415
Don't go away, son.

744
01:33:07,615 --> 01:33:08,655
It won't break us.

745
01:33:08,895 --> 01:33:11,535
Body first, bones later.

746
01:33:12,255 --> 01:33:14,995
And only dust remains.

747
01:33:15,275 --> 01:33:16,007
Stop now!

748
01:33:16,207 --> 01:33:17,248
Be quiet!

749
01:33:17,615 --> 01:33:19,395
They cannot silence the truth.

750
01:33:19,855 --> 01:33:21,415
They make it noisier.

751
01:33:21,635 --> 01:33:24,075
Like the drums that foretell...

752
01:33:24,275 --> 01:33:25,275
Death!

753
01:33:33,746 --> 01:33:35,347
Oh, ya, ya.

754
01:33:35,547 --> 01:33:37,035
What's wrong, little monkey?

755
01:33:41,535 --> 01:33:42,595
Yes, yes, yes!

756
01:33:47,066 --> 01:33:49,164
Oh, thank you so much!

757
01:33:49,364 --> 01:33:50,637
YOUR HIGHNESS!

